### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

Don't known / other

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

I create an app with "ng new --ssr", I added some libraries as "ionic" and was trying to set it up with ssr.

So If I test aplicacion on local with "ionic serve", it uses architect "app:serve".

When I go to see the App localy I ended up with this warning:

> NG0505: Angular hydration was requested on the client, but there was no serialized information present in the server response, thus hydration was not enabled. Make sure the `provideClientHydration()` 
![Captura de pantalla 2024-01-21 a la(s) 14 45 49](https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/36543775/cb9c6886-5975-43e3-9694-f8590d682318)


So i deactivate using "provideClientHydration", so it looks fine on local
<img width="1634" alt="Captura de pantalla 2024-01-21 a la(s) 15 24 50" src="https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/36543775/6c9f0182-52e5-462a-98f4-e0e5a3b02bbc">

But, when I try to do "ionic build", which uses "app:build", I got the static version which looks clearly different, that´s because shado dom is not added. I´ve also tried activating or deactivating but got any difference.  (https://foodjourney.app/welcome)

